long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: In manual partitioning, when you try to create a partition when there's no more space left, you'll receive a "local variable 'e' referenced before assignment" error dialog as explanation.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): anaconda 24.13.7-1
How reproducible: always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. boot F24 netinst 2. go to manual partitioning 3. I had a clean disk, but you can probably just remove all partitions on disk 4. create / partition occupying the whole disk 5. try to create /boot partition of some size (100M) 6. see an error bar on bottom 7. click it and see "local variable 'e' referenced before assignment"
